<title>UK: British Energy sales rise in December.</title>
<headline>British Energy sales rise in December.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-01-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>Nuclear electricity producer British Energy Plc said on Monday that total sales reached 6.18 Terawatt hours (TWh) in December from 5.80 a year ago.</p>
<p>A Terawatt hour is the largest unit of measurement for electricity sales, representing one billion kilowatt hours.</p>
<p>The following table details sales from each power station in TWh. Comparisons are with the year-ago month:</p>
<p>  Station		   December 1996	     December 1995</p>
<p>  Hinkley Point B		0.83			  0.86</p>
<p>  Hunterston B		   0.86			  0.79</p>
<p>  Dungeness B		    0.67			  0.00</p>
<p>  Heysham 1			0.71			  0.84</p>
<p>  Hartlepool		     0.71			  0.55</p>
<p>  Torness			  0.82			  0.90</p>
<p>  Heysham 2			0.77			  0.98</p>
<p>  Sizewell B		     0.81			  0.88</p>
<p>  Total			    6.18			  5.80</p>
<p>British Energy said total sales to customers in the year to date were 49.69 TWh, versus 44.56 TWh a year ago.</p>
<p>-- London Newsroom +44 171 542 7717</p>
